       Developing Microsoft Dynamics GP Business Applications - 2010kaiser
       ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


Microsoft Dynamics GP is a sophisticated Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) application with a multitude of features and options. Microsoft Dynamics GP can also be used to develop dynamic, mission critical applications. &quot;Developing Microsoft Dynamics GP Business Applications&quot; will take you through the complex steps of creating and customizing Microsoft Dynamics GP applications. Starting with an overview of Microsoft Dynamics GP architecture you'll then move onto setting up your development environment. You will learn how to make your application come to life with Dexterity and sanScript. You will create table operations and ranges as well as object triggers to make powerful and practical business applications. You will deploy your Dexterity solution before moving onto customization with Modifier and VBA. This book will also take you through ways of enhancing and extending your application without code using the SmartList Builder and Excel Report Builder. Using these highly flexible tools you'll be able to create data connections that will increase the usability and functionality of your ERP applications.

What you will learn from this book:
===================================

1. Discover the ins and outs of Microsoft Dynamics GP Architecture.
2. Utilize Dexterity and sanScript to build business applications.
3. Learn the correct use and implementation of object triggers.
4. Modify your application without code.
5. Utilize VBA to extend your business application.
6. Discover how to use Visual Studio tools.
7. Upgrade Dexterity applications.

Title: Developing Microsoft Dynamics GP Business Applications
Author: Leslie Vail
Publisher: Packt Publishing
Year: 2012
Format: PDF-EPUB-MOBI

